Combine whole wheat flour and yeast in a large bowl. Stir in sugar, baking soda, baking powder, and water. Stir in anise seeds. Let dough stand in warm area for 1 hour, letting bread rise. Knead bread and put in 2 regular loaf pans. Brush tops with beaten egg whites. Bake at 400 degrees F (205 degrees C) for 50 minutes. Enjoy!